ite an often stated desire to return to the private sector. In his last private sector job he headed the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the world's second largest futures market <PERSON> Yeutter </PERSON>, who has four children, grew up on a <LOCATION> Nebraska </LOCATION> farm and still manages a 2,500 property in the town of <LOCATION> Cozad </LOCATION>.
