</TEXT>
<HEAD>1964</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 JAN. 17 _ <ORGANIZATION> Arab </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> summit in <LOCATION> Cairo </LOCATION> establishes <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Ahmed </PERSON> <PERSON> Shukairi </PERSON>, Palestinian delegate to league, later was elected chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION>, which became the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>'s legislature.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1965</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 JAN. 1 _ <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> forms <ORGANIZATION> Fatah </ORGANIZATION> guerrilla group.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1967</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 JUNE 5-11 _ <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> captures <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Golan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Heights </LOCATION> in a Six-Day War. NOV. 22 _ <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> passes Resolution 242 recognizing <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s right to exist. <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> rejects the resolution, which refers to Palestinians only as refugees and does not address their claim to independent homeland.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1969</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 FEB. 4 _ <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> elects <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> chairman of <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> Executive Committee, succeeding <PERSON> Shukairi </PERSON>.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1970</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 SEPTEMBER _ King <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION>, alarmed by growing Palestinian power, sends his army to drive guerrillas out of <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> moves his base to <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. Series of aircraft hijackings in early 1970s cause widespread condemnation of the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1971</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 NOV. 28 _ Black September, new Palestinian group seeking revenge on <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION>, assassinates <PERSON> Wasfi </PERSON> <PERSON> Tal </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Jordanian </LOCATION> prime minister.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1972</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 SEPT. 5 _ Black September terrorists seize <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> athletes at Olympic Games in <LOCATION> Munich </LOCATION>, and 11 Israelis and five Palestinians are killed.
