<HEAD>Legislators Increase Own Pay By 85 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 In a rare show of unity, ruling and opposition lawmakers today approved without debate legislation that will raise their salaries by 85 percent on Jan. 1. The two-minute action raised a lawmaker's monthly salary from the current $ 2,550 to $ 4,730, bringing their pay to the level of Cabinet ministers. The bill was approved by the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Budget </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Settlement </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>. It's passage by the full assembly will be a mere formality. Many South Koreans criticized the steep pay increase as unethical, citing the meager incomes of most factory workers and high inflation. According to industry figures, a footwear assembly line worker with five years of job experience makes about $ 550 a month, including allowances.
