<HEAD>Men Stranded on Glacier After Small Plane Makes Emergency Landing</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BRIAN S. AKRE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JUNEAU, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A snowstorm forced rescuers to leave two men stranded on a glacier in southeast <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> for a second day after their small plane made an emergency landing on the remote river of ice. Once visibility improved today, <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> officials planned to send a helicopter to pick up the men, who messaged by radio that they were unhurt and wearing survival gear, said <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> Lt. <PERSON> Rick </PERSON> <PERSON> Ehret </PERSON>. `` They gave every indication that they're still in very good shape, are nice and warm, have plenty of food and can stand another night on the glacier,'' <PERSON> Ehret </PERSON> said Wednesday. The 1940s-vintage <PERSON> Grumman </PERSON> <PERSON> Widgeon </PERSON> amphibious plane landed about 100 miles northwest of <LOCATION> Juneau </LOCATION> on Grand Pacific Glacier on Tuesday afternoon, <PERSON> Ehret </PERSON> said. The plane was not damaged and the men were waiting inside it. The men contacted passing commercial and military jets by radio late Tuesday and their distress calls were relayed to the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Juneau </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Ehret </PERSON> said. Pilot <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Mills </PERSON>, 38, and passenger <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> `` Buddy'' <PERSON> Ferguson </PERSON>, 31, of <PERSON> Gustavus </PERSON>, were flying from <PERSON> Cordova </PERSON> to <PERSON> Gustavus </PERSON> when they were forced to land about 45 miles from their destination for an unknown reason, <PERSON> Ehret </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Mills </PERSON>' wife, <PERSON> Connie </PERSON>, said both men were professional pilots who had recently restored the plane. The <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> dispatched an H-3 helicopter Wednesday morning to rescue the men, but the craft ran int