<PERSON> Wapner </PERSON> _ for <ORGANIZATION> ` </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>.' <PERSON> Goldberg </PERSON> scoffed at the credibility of <PERSON> Capasso </PERSON>'s former British-born housekeeper, <PERSON> Shirley </PERSON> <PERSON> Harrod </PERSON>, and likened her gossipy testimony to the public television series `` Upstairs, Downstairs,'' about a wealthy British family and its servants. `` How important was it that you learn <PERSON> Bess </PERSON> <PERSON> Myerson </PERSON> did n't want people to know she was sleeping _ this is the'80s, now _ that she was sleeping with <PERSON> Andy </PERSON> <PERSON> Capasso </PERSON>?'' <PERSON> Goldberg </PERSON> asked rhetorically. He maintained that <PERSON> Capasso </PERSON>'s ex-wife had instigated the case because she was dissatisfied with the divorce settlement. `` What a tragedy that we're here because <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Capasso </PERSON> has sold the government a bill of goods that wo n't hold up,'' said <PERSON> Goldberg </PERSON>.
