<HEAD>State Orders Full Environmental Review for Walden Project</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CHRISTOPHER B. DALY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Government is best that governs least, according to <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Thoreau </PERSON>, but a state order for a full environmental review of a proposed project near his beloved <LOCATION> Walden </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pond </LOCATION> may keep development of the area at bay. `` We are <LOCATION> Walden </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pond </LOCATION>'s caretakers,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> DeVillars </PERSON>, the state's newly named secretary of the <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, which called for the lengthy review on Wednesday. `` Our responsibility is to ensure that we take every reasonable measure to avoid or minimize damage to this historic area. Nothing short of a full review will fulfill that responsibility,'' <PERSON> DeVillars </PERSON> said. At issue is a proposed <ORGANIZATION> Concord </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Park </ORGANIZATION> by the developer <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Properties </ORGANIZATION>, which wants to build a 148,000-square-foot office building and a 518-car parking area. The land is near where <PERSON> Thoreau </PERSON> worked on his masterpiece, `` <PERSON> Walden </PERSON>,'' while living there in solitude beginning in 1845 for two years in a hut on land owned by <PERSON> Ralph </PERSON> <PERSON> Waldo </PERSON> <PERSON> Emerson </PERSON>. In the book, <PERSON> Thoreau </PERSON> writes about the importance being close to nature. The land later was donated to <LOCATION> Middlesex </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> and eventually to the state, which maintains the heavily used recreation area around the pond. Some preservation groups have urged the state to buy the land and add it to the <ORGANIZATION> Walden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reservation </ORGANIZATION> surrounding the pristine