<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 The following is a summary of recent statements by <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>: _ In <LOCATION> Algiers </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Algeria </LOCATION>, on Nov. 15, the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>'s parliament, declared a Palestinian state with <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> as its capital `` The state of <LOCATION> Palestine </LOCATION> herewith declares that it believes in the settlement of regional and international disputes by peaceful means, in accordance with the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> Charter and resolutions,'' <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> said in reading the declaration. The council endorsed key <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> resolutions that implicitly call for recognition of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s right to exist.
