 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> AGREES TO TALKS _ President <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> says <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s statement fulfills long-standing <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> conditions and authorizes the <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> to `` enter into a substantive dialogue with <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> representatives. Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> designates the <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> ambassador in <LOCATION> Tunisia </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Pelletreau </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, as `` the only authorized channel'' for dialogue with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> also says the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was not recognizing the Palestinian state declared by the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> last month, and he reiterates an `` unflinching'' <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> commitment to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s security.
