 A 2 -LCB- - year-old girl was taken to a hospital suffering from hallucinations and seizures apparently caused by a cocaine overdose, authorities said today The child was taken to <ORGANIZATION> Cedars-Sinai </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> shortly after 9 p.m. Wednesday, said police Sgt. <PERSON> K. </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>. A urinalysis revealed the child had ingested cocaine, said hospital spokeswoman <PERSON> Paula </PERSON> <PERSON> Correia </PERSON>. The toddler was listed in fair condition in the medical center's pediatric intensive-care unit, Ms. <PERSON> Correia </PERSON> said. Police and officials from the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Children </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> were investigating, <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> said. `` The parents are saying they do n't know how it all happened,'' he said. `` The mother said she dropped off the girl at her sister's, who then dropped off the girl at a day care center.'' The parents, who were n't identified, told police they noticed the child acting strangely when they picked her up from the center, <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> said. Sgt. <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Crosby </PERSON> said the child was picked up by an ambulance at a day care center after a caller reported the child was having a seizure. He said he did not know the name of the day care center, which is located in south-central <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, an area notorious for gangs and drug dealing. The child's family also lives in the area.
