<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> met today with <ORGANIZATION> East </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> German </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leader <PERSON> Erich </PERSON> <PERSON> Honecker </PERSON>, the state news agency <ORGANIZATION> ADN </ORGANIZATION> said. After meeting with the East German leaders <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> left for <LOCATION> Bucharest </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> ADN </ORGANIZATION> said. The agency issued a statement saying the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> decision Wednesday to open a dialogue with the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> `` can only be beneficial'' to <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> peace efforts. <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> arrived in <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION>, where he addressed the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION>, and was there for a working visit, <ORGANIZATION> ADN </ORGANIZATION> said. `` Both sides agreed that ... an international peace conference under the auspices of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION>, with the participation of the five permanent members of the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> as well as all interested sides, including the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, is the only way'' to a comprehensive and lasting peace in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> ADN </ORGANIZATION> said.
