6th graf, `The singer ...'</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARY BROOKS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>AIKEN, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> failed to heed an officer's flashing blue lights and siren, the lawman testified today at the soul singer's assault trial Sheriff's Deputy <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Danner </PERSON> said he pulled alongside <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>'s truck several times Sept. 24 and the singer swerved as if trying to run him off the road <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, known as the Godfather of Soul, also allegedly attempted to run over two <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Augusta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> officers. He is charged with assault with intent to kill and failure to stop for police. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> `` had a total disregard for his surroundings,'' <PERSON> Danner </PERSON> said in his report of that day's events. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, 55, testified Wednesday that he did n't pull over during the chase through <LOCATION> Augusta </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ga. </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Augusta </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> S.C. </LOCATION>, because, `` I was scared to death.'' `` I went to <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> and I was n't that frightened,'' he said. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said he initially was n't aware of the first two officers who attempted to pull him over. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> seemed somewhat confused about the sequence of events. The singer, wearing a gray suit and blue satin shirt, testified that he did n't remember driving more than 80 mph. When he did stop, he said, the officers scared him by shooting at his truck and banging on the windows. Meanwhile, Judge <PERSON> Hubert </PERSON> <PERSON> Long </PERSON> rejected defense arguments that authorities acted recklessly during the pursuit. `` Even if the officers made a mistake and endangered the public, I do n't see what that has to do with ... a man who failed to stop for a blue light,'' the judge said. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> could receive up to 30 years in prison if convicted.
