<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, once a ragtag army of militants pursuing the quixotic aim of crushing <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, has evolved into a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> government-in-waiting embracing a wide range of ideologies. But the unity is fragile. The nine guerrilla factions and other political groups which constitute the 23-year-old movement are held together by their Palestinian nationalism. They are prey to the divisive and violent currents of <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> politics. They range from the Marxist guerrillas of <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Habash </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> Popular </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> for the <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION>, which endorsed <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s strategy of moderation with some reluctance, to Islamic fundamentalists The outcome of the talks will be crucial for <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s strategy of moderation. That depends to a large degree on him holding the radical elements of his disparate organization in check long enough to attain solid political gains _ not just from the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, but from <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> represents a widely divergent constituency in the 5.5 million strong Palestinian diaspora, from poor peasants eking a living on the scrubland of the Israeli-occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> to intellectuals in Western capitals. Some, like <PERSON> Habash </PERSON>, are Greek Orthodox Christians. Most, like <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>, are Moslems. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> is more than just a military organization dedicated to regaining the Palestinian homeland lost in 1948. <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>, 59, has built it into an institution that