<BYLINE>By JIM DRINKARD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Asociated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Leading members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> gave the new opening between the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> a wary welcome Thursday and sought to reassure <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> that <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials will be alert to any <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> tricks. `` This is good news and the right path to follow,'' said Sen. <PERSON> Claiborne </PERSON> <PERSON> Pell </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-R.I. </LOCATION>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>. `` I think we would best be very careful that the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> continue to show real seriousness and be wary of any deception.'' Sen. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON>, the newly elected <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> majority leader, welcomed the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> move and called it a `` significant step toward advancing the peace process.'' `` It is consistent with what has been bipartisan American policy for over a decade,'' <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Maine </LOCATION>, said in a statement. `` Under that policy, the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> seeks to encourage direct negotiations between the parties, without preconditions, intended to achieve a stable and lasting peace.'' <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s acceptance of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s right to exist and renunciation of terrorism were `` important statements'' but `` in light of the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>'s record ... must be viewed with caution. He added that the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> action `` in no way represents or implies ...