asurer <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Capet </PERSON> said the bad investments were made over a 6 - to 8-month period He said the assets were purchased at a high price and sold at a lower price. Former Assistant Treasurer <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Lester </PERSON>, who actually made the investments under <PERSON> Margolin </PERSON>, was quoted in The <ORGANIZATION> Charleston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gazette </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday as saying that she was retaining a lawyer and would have no comment. Assistant Treasurer <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON>, who now is in charge of investments, said the consolidated investment fund this week totaled $ 1.572 billion, or $ 208 million less than last December. The fund was $ 2.4 billion at the end of 1986.
