<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Fierce winds ripped across <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> and ice pellets and snow fell in the central coastal area of the state Thursday, while up to 18 inches of snow fell in <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Upper </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Peninsula </LOCATION>. Northward winds in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> were clocked at 102 mph early Thursday atop Mt. Diablo about 40 miles east of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>. Hurricane force winds are 74 mph or greater. The winds caused at least one death, overturned trucks and cut power to more than 440,000 electric customers. Winds gusted to 67 mph at <ORGANIZATION> Travis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Base </ORGANIZATION> and to 54 mph on the Golden Gate Bridge in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>. One to 2 inches of wet snow fell in the higher elevations near <LOCATION> Paso </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Robles </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>. Ice pellets and snowshowers were reported over the <LOCATION> Inland </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION> of <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Barbara </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> A snow advisory was in effect for the higher elevations of the southern <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> deserts through Friday. Early Thursday, winds in northern <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION> blew trailers off their foundations at <ORGANIZATION> Utah </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Logan </LOCATION>. Winds gusted to 105 mph at <LOCATION> Centerville </LOCATION>, 84 mph at <LOCATION> Logan </LOCATION> and 74 mph at <ORGANIZATION> Hill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Base </ORGANIZATION>. The winds knocked out power to 50,0