l signs to the contrary. <PERSON> Norman </PERSON> and his wife, <PERSON> Judith </PERSON>, originally were charged with homicide by abuse. The charge against the <PERSON> Norman </PERSON> was later reduced to first-degree manslaughter and charges against Mrs. <PERSON> Norman </PERSON> were dismissed. Charges of second-degree criminal mistreatment also are pending against three other former sect leaders, whose trials are scheduled for next year. The fellowship, which at its peak claimed about 300 adult members in four states, disbanded in February.
