<TEXT>
 `` Drugs are everywhere _ in the workplace, movie industry, sports fields and college campuses.'' _ <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s spokeswoman <PERSON> Elaine </PERSON> <PERSON> Crispen </PERSON>, after disclosure July 1 that two <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> secretaries had resigned and three <ORGANIZATION> Secret </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> officers were suspended during a drug probe.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 `` <PERSON> Bobby </PERSON> <PERSON> Knight </PERSON> told me this: ` There is nothing that a good defense can not beat a better offense.' In other words, a good offense wins.'' `` We all lived in this century - I did n't live in this century - in this century's history We did not have - as a matter of fact, we fought - Hitlerism.'' `` First, I'd say a prayer for myself and for the country that I'm about to lead. _ Vice President-elect <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>, on the campaign trail.
