 `` What I think it does is spell the end of the user-friendly era.'' _ <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> tenEyck </PERSON>, telecommunications director of the <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Computer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION>, following the sabotage of 6,000 computers nationwide in November by a computer virus.
