</TEXT>
<HEAD>TOP SINGLE RECORD</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` Faith'' by <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> on <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Records </ORGANIZATION>. -LRB- Billboard magazine. -RRB-
</TEXT>
<HEAD>TOP BROADWAY SHOW</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` The Phantom of the Opera.'' The <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Webber </PERSON> musical has sold out since it opened last January, grossing $ 27.54 million for the year. By New Year's Eve, 667,896 people will have seen the show at the Majestic Theater.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>MOST-WATCHED TELEVISION PROGRAM (INDIVIDUAL)</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 Super Bowl XXII on Jan. 31, when 110 million people tuned in to watch the <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Redskins </ORGANIZATION> defeat the <ORGANIZATION> Denver </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broncos </ORGANIZATION>.
</TEXT>
