<HEAD>Larry Adler, Rags-To-Riches Immigrant, Dead At 57</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Adler </PERSON>, a Hungarian refugee from World War II who arrived in <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> penniless and became one of its leading business tycoons, has died at age 57 of complications following a heart attack. <PERSON> Adler </PERSON>, who died Tuesday, was chairman and chief executive of <ORGANIZATION> FAI </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurances </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, one of <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>'s largest companies. The cause of death was not given other than that it was related to a Dec. 2 heart attack. Known as a shrewd and sometimes ruthless workaholic, <PERSON> Adler </PERSON> once described work as something to `` play at.'' `` I work golf, I work tennis, but I play work,'' he told a newspaper interviewer three years ago. `` I absolutely love it and if another heart attack is the price I have to pay to keep going at this pace, then I'll pay it gladly.'' <PERSON> Adler </PERSON> claimed that money itself was not the prime motive for his constant striving. `` Sure, it's important when you have n't got it. But once you have it, it is merely a barometer of how well you are doing,'' he said. `` Money is the only applause a businessman gets for his performance.'' Arriving in the country in 1949, <PERSON> Adler </PERSON> worked as a gas station attendant, record-shop owner and taxi driver before forming Fire & amp; <ORGANIZATION> All </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Risks </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> in 1960 with $ 56,000 cash. <ORGANIZATION> FAI </ORGANIZATION> is a $ 2 billion-a-year business, and is listed on exchanges in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Toronto </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Switzerland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Zealand </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Singapore </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Laszlo </PERSON