<HEAD>Primerica, Commercial Credit Shareholders Vote On Merger</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LINDA STOWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Commercial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Credit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 1.65 billion cash and stock buyout of <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> was approved overwhelmingly by shareholders of both companies on Thursday, despite criticism by some <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION> workers and shareholders of big severance payments for the company's executives. `` I only wish the powers that protected the executive board would have protected the employees a little more,'' said <PERSON> Lorraine </PERSON> <PERSON> Cheney </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION> employee for three years. <LOCATION> Cheney </LOCATION> and some others said their benefits have been cut, while top executives of <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION> are receiving severance payments, called golden parachutes, that reportedly total about $ 98 million. Under the buyout, shareholders will receive one share of <ORGANIZATION> Commercial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Credit </ORGANIZATION> common stock plus $ 7 in cash for each share of <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION>. Based on Thursday's closing price, the deal is worth $ 28.25 a share in cash and stock. <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION> closed at $ 28 a share on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. The combined companies will operate under the <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION> name. <ORGANIZATION> Primerica </ORGANIZATION>, a Greenwich-based financial services and direct-marketing company, is the parent of <ORGANIZATION> Smith </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Barney </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Harris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Upham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZ